        |Rovers: A NGO founded to facilitate learning, exploring and experiencing of different
        |cultures and heritage. The organisation started with an initiative to educate students about
        |the culture and heritage of India through the mode of study programmes and practical
        |exposure. India is vast, diverse and the oldest thriving civilization so, our study programmes
        |aspire to make travel, learning and living parallel processes to stimulate growth in an
        |individual developing a sense of pride. We want to make travel a mode of educating instead
        |of leisure by engaging students in group workshops, individual activities which would bring
        |out the best in each.
